copy the USS files from one location to another 
cp -rf /usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v312/usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v3r12/ /usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v312/ 
r = Recursively copy all files and directories
f = option can overwrite important files without warning. Be sure that overwriting files is intended
cp -mprv /usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v312/usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v3r12/ /usr/lpp/IBM/cyp/v312/ 
-m: Preserve mode (permissions) of the files.
-p: Preserve file attributes (such as timestamps and ownership).
-r: Copy directories recursively.
-v: Verbose output, showing files as they are copied.
